Subject: Dictated Math Toolchain Install Source

Description: Preserved source request to install useful tools for Riemann Hypothesis fundamentals work.

& [DictatedMathToolchainInstallSource] is the preserved user request
  + [source_status] is preserved_raw_request
  + [captured_request] is install what tools would be useful in this work
  + [active_project] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis
  + [toolchain_goal] is provide a clean local programmatic loop for math operations, tests, tables, plots, graph analysis, and feedback records
  + [authority_boundary] is source request only until reflected into toolchain requirements and verified installation
  + [inside] is project-local Python virtual environment, requirements file, useful math and analysis packages, and installation verification
  + [outside] is proof machinery, remote services, hidden credentials, global environment mutation, and untracked generated virtualenv contents

  = must: prefer project-local environment over global mutation
  = must: preserve tool selection as support for analysis, not proof
  = must: verify installed tools before relying on them
  - never: treat installed packages as theorem authority
